  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Feature or Bug? i.e Type: Bug)\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Describe the feature you would like, or briefly summarise the bug and what you did, what you expected to happen, and what actually happens. Sections below)\r\n*Summary*: `Transaction failed. Replacement transaction underpriced` error happens when a recovered user with funds sends a transaction. For now it already happened when sending a transaction from wallet to an address, to a contact in 1-1 chat and when deploying a contract from Status Test DApp and for both ETH and tokens\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nTransaction is successfully sent\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n`Transaction failed. Replacement transaction underpriced` error is shown after sending a transaction and clicking Got it button\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/29711298/43570497-c3b248b8-963a-11e8-9253-4ad4ca888bdd.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n[comment]: # (Describe how we can replicate the bug step by step.)\r\n\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Recover an account of user with funds\r\n- Send a transaction \r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n[comment]: # (Please do your best to fill this out.)\r\n* Status version: 0.9.24 (6289) node 7ebe0c3\r\n* Operating System: Android 7.1\r\n\r\n#### Logs\r\n[geth.log](https://github.com/status-im/status-react/files/2294277/geth.log)\r\n[TF.log](https://github.com/status-im/status-react/files/2294294/TF.log)\r\nTF session: https://app.testfairy.com/projects/4803622-status/builds/8559654/sessions/4398752145?source=latest-sessions\r\n",
